# Firebase Configuration for SrijanVerse Admin

Add these environment variables to `.env.local` in your project root:

```
VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=your_api_key
VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=your_project.firebaseapp.com
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your_project_id
VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=your_project.appspot.com
VITE_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=your_sender_id
VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=your_app_id
VITE_FIREBASE_MEASUREMENT_ID=G-0YHTZNC7JW
```

## Setup Instructions:

1. Go to [Firebase Console](https://console.firebase.google.com/)
2. Create a new project or select existing one
3. Go to Project Settings → Service Accounts
4. Copy the Web app config values
5. Create `.env.local` file in project root with the credentials above
6. Enable Email/Password authentication in Firebase Console → Authentication → Sign-in method

## First-Time Admin Setup:

1. Create an admin account in Firebase Console or use the login form (Firebase will auto-create with Email/Password auth enabled)
2. Use that email/password to login via the admin panel
